      • getAvailability

        private boolean getAvailability()
        there is an issue with this method: if it is called often enough, the _s.sendUrgentData(0); method that it invokes, will force the _s socket to close on the other end, at least on Windows systems. This behavior is due to the fact that OOB data handling is problematic since there are conflicting specifications in TCP. Therefore, it is required that the method is not called with high frequency (see the PDBTExecInitedSrv._CHECK_PERIOD_MSECS flag in this file.)
        Returns:
        true iff the worker is available to accept work according to all evidence.
